# .dockerignore — what Docker must NOT copy into the build context.
#
# The "build context" is everything Docker sends to the daemon when you run
# `docker build .`. Smaller context = faster builds and no accidental secrets
# or junk baked into image layers. This is the Docker cousin of .gitignore.

# Host-installed dependencies. CRITICAL: these were compiled for YOUR machine
# (macOS / arm64). The image is Linux (alpine). Copying them in would ship the
# wrong-architecture binaries — `npm ci` inside the build installs fresh, correct
# Linux ones. So we exclude them AND let the build reinstall.
node_modules

# Build outputs — regenerated inside the image by `npm run build`. No reason to
# ship the host's copies (and they'd just bloat the context).
.next
out

# Version control + CI metadata — irrelevant to building/serving the app.
.git
.github
.gitignore

# Vercel local link/config — not needed to build the container.
.vercel

# Local env files — never bake secrets into an image.
.env*

# OS / editor cruft.
.DS_Store
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# The Docker files themselves don't need to be in the context.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
